<p>Monday 6th August 1917<br/>745 am Stopped by German raider "Wolf &amp; prize crew took charge. Self &amp; officers sent onboard "Wolf". We were sighted the previous evening at 6pm by <u>Seaplane.</u><br/>"Wolf's" armament - : 7 &ndash; 6" guns, 4 torpedo tubes [indecipherable] <u>Machine guns</u><br/>10.30 Both ships proceeded in N. Ely direction giving New Zealand a wide berth.<br/>Officer Lieut. Rosa who took charge of Matunga informed me that he had been waiting 3 days for us, having picked up a wireless message from Sydney about our coal</p>
